<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2592] CQL greater-than and less-than operators (&gt; and &lt;) result in key ranges that are inclusive of the terms</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2592</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This affects range queries against keys, but not index queries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One possible solution: let the coordinator strip out the extra row in QueryProcessor.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
